íŸ@cc3c8e3d8b0f8c49d2d2e9713412dd219ac53ba3e5dc55773d744704cc508800⁄$Title: title: str ends-with
Path: Examples
Content:
Checks if string ends with '.rb'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'my_library.rb' | str ends-with '.rb'
true

```
Checks if strings end with '.txt'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ['my_library.rb', 'README.txt'] | str ends-with '.txt'
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ false ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ true  ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
Checks if string ends with '.RB', case-insensitive.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'my_library.rb' | str ends-with --ignore-case '.RB'
true

```
